# Dev: `.env.development` uses `/api/v1` (Vite proxy → localhost:8005).
#
# Vercel + API on Render (recommended):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api/v1
#   BACKEND_ORIGIN=https://your-api.onrender.com   (no trailing slash, no /api/v1)
# Edge middleware (frontend/middleware.js) proxies /api/v1 → BACKEND_ORIGIN.
# Ensure BACKEND_ORIGIN is enabled for Edge in Vercel (not “Sensitive”-only if that blocks Edge).
#
# Fallback if proxy still fails: point the browser straight at the API (set CORS on Render):
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com/api/v1
#
# Root Directory `frontend` → uses frontend/middleware.js + frontend/vercel.json.
# Root Directory `.` → uses repo middleware.js + root vercel.json.
#
# Or call the API directly (set CORS + FRONTEND_ORIGIN on the server):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com/api/v1
